  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. The 6 non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3. CFD predictions of relative hemolysis index satisfy the RH < 1 acceptance criterion across all 5 operating points. The assessment team concludes that the computational model provides sufficient credibility to support the COU decision regarding worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The methodology for hemolysis scalar transport employed here follows the approach reviewed in the computational hemolysis literature, including the recent survey by Ding et al. (2024) (doi:10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003), which consolidates best practices for power-law hemolysis model calibration and validation — a reference that informed the rationale for factor assessments in this package.",
